How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion, dating apps are the best way to find the right person for you. I have been using them for a while now and I have met some great people. It is much easier, quicker and more efficent to find people who line up with more of what you want in a person. You are also more likely to find new things that you like about people because you are exposed to many more then trying to pick a mate out a club or anywhere else. You literally have access to hundreds or thousands of single people in your area using these apps. Many more fish in the sea that your can potentially catch.

How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion, dating apps are the best way to find the right person for you. I have been using them for a while now and I have met some great people. It is much easier, quicker and more efficent to find people who line up with more of what you want in a person. You are also more likely to find new things that you like about people because you are exposed to many more then trying to pick a mate out a club or anywhere else. You literally have access to hundreds or thousands of single people in your area using these apps. Many more fish in the sea that you can potentially catch.  have also found that the people who use these apps are more serious about finding someone. if that is what your are looking for or the exact opposite is always available

---

In my opinion, dating apps are the best way to find the right person for you. I have been using them for a while now and I have met some great people. You are also more likely to find new things that you like about people because you are exposed to many more then trying to pick a mate out a club or anywhere else. How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion, dating apps are the best way to find the right person for you. I have been using them for a while now and I have met some great people. It is much easier, quicker and more efficent to find people who line up with more of what you want in a person. You are also more likely to find new things that you like about people because you are exposed to many more then trying to pick a mate out a club or anywhere else. You literally have access to hundreds or thousands of single people in your area using these apps. Many more fish in the sea that you can potentially catch.  have also found that the people who use these apps are more serious about finding someone. if that is what your are looking for or the exact opposite is always available if that will tickle your fancy. Its also way safer to meet someone online and interact with them first before meeting them in person. You can get a good feel for a person using all the tools at your disposal. How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion, dating apps are the best way to find the right person for you. I have been using them for a while now and I have met some great people. It is much easier, quicker and more efficent to find people who line up with more of what you want in a person. You are also more likely to find new things that you like about people because you are exposed to many more then trying to pick a mate out a club or anywhere else. You literally have access to hundreds or thousands of single people in your area using these apps. Many more fish in the sea that you can potentially catch.  have also found that the people who use these apps are more serious about finding someone. if that is what your are looking for or the exact opposite is always available if that will tickle your fancy. Its also way safer to meet someone online and interact with them first before meeting them in person. You can get a good feel for a person using all the tools at your disposal. How Do You Think Technology Affects Dating?

Have you had any experience with dating? Have you ever used dating apps? If so, what has it been like for you? If not, why not?

How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion, dating apps are the best way to find the right person for you. I have been using them for a while now and I have met some great people. It is much easier, quicker and more efficent to find people who line up with more of what you want in a person. You are also more likely to find new things that you like about people because you are exposed to many more then trying to pick a mate out a club or anywhere else. You literally have access to hundreds or thousands of single people in your area using these apps. Many more fish in the sea that you can potentially catch.  have also found that the people who use these apps are more serious about finding someone. if that is what your are looking for or the exact opposite is always available if that will tickle your fancy. Its also way safer to meet someone online and interact with them first before meeting them in person. You can get a good feel for a person using all the tools at your disposal. You can see their pictures, read their profile, see what they like and dislike all while talking to them in real time. I realize that you feelings may all change when you meet in person but its still much more efficient then trying to find people in person. The algorithms used to match people are also getting better and better as time goes and the tools that go along with them.

How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion, dating apps are the best way to find the right person for you. I have been using them for a while now and I have met some great people. It is much easier, quicker and more efficent to find people who line up with more of what you want in a person. You are also more likely to find new things that you like about people because you are exposed to many more then trying to pick a mate out a club or anywhere else. You literally have access to hundreds or thousands of single people in your area using these apps. Many more fish in the sea that you can potentially catch.  have also found that the people who use these apps are more serious about finding someone. if that is what your are looking for or the exact opposite is always available if that will tickle your fancy. Its also way safer to meet someone online and interact with them first before meeting them in person. You can get a good feel for a person using all the tools at your disposal. You can see their pictures, read their profile, see what they like and dislike all while talking to them in real time. I realize that you feelings may all change when you meet in person but its still much more efficient then trying to find people in person. The algorithms used to match people are also getting better and better as time goes and the tools that go along with them.

---

It is much easier, quicker and more efficent to find people who line up with more of what you want in a person. You are also more likely to find new things that you like about people because you are exposed to many more then trying to pick a mate out a club or anywhere else. You literally have access to hundreds or thousands of single people in your area using these apps. Many more fish in the sea that you can potentially catch.  have also found that the people who use these apps are more serious about finding someone. if that is what your are looking for or the exact opposite is always available if that will tickle your fancy. Its also way safer to meet someone online and interact with them first before meeting them in person. You can get a good feel for a person using all the tools at your disposal. You can see their pictures, read their profile, see what they like and dislike all while talking to them in real time. I realize that you feelings may all change when you meet in person but its still much more efficient then trying to find people in person. The algorithms used to match people are also getting better and better as time goes and the tools that go along with them.

How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion, dating apps are the best way to find the right person for you. I have been using them for a while now and I have met some great people. It is much easier, quicker and more efficent to find people who line up with more of what you want in a person. You are also more likely to find new things that you like about people because you are exposed to many more then trying to pick a mate out a club or anywhere else. You literally have access to hundreds or thousands of single people in your area using these apps. Many more fish in the sea that you can potentially catch.  have also found that the people who use these apps are more serious about finding someone. if that is what your are looking for or the exact opposite is always available if that will tickle your fancy. Its also way safer to meet someone online and interact with them first before meeting them in person. You can get a good feel for a person using all the tools at your disposal. You can see their pictures, read their profile, see what they like and dislike all while talking to them in real time. I realize that you feelings may all change when you meet in person but its still much more efficient then trying to find people in person. The algorithms used to match people are also getting better and better as time goes and the tools that go along with them. 
While I realize dating apps are not for everyone, but they are useful to most. They are much better at finding you a mate then your are in a personal setting. Not just a little better but several orders of magnitude better. I pe

Have you had any experience with dating? Have you ever used dating apps? If so, what has it been like for you? If not, why not?

How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion, dating apps are the best way to find the right person for you. I have been using them for a while now and I have met some great people. It is much easier, quicker and more efficent to find people who line up with more of what you want in a person. You are also more likely to find new things that you like about people because you are exposed to many more then trying to pick a mate out a club or anywhere else. You literally have access to hundreds or thousands of single people in your area using these apps. Many more fish in the sea that you can potentially catch.  have also found that the people who use these apps are more serious about finding someone. if that is what your are looking for or the exact opposite is always available if that will tickle your fancy. Its also way safer to meet someone online and interact with them first before meeting them in person. You can get a good feel for a person using all the tools at your disposal. You can see their pictures, read their profile, see what they like and dislike all while talking to them in real time. I realize that you feelings may all change when you meet in person but its still much more efficient then trying to find people in person. The algorithms used to match people are also getting better and better as time goes and the tools that go along with them. 
While I realize dating apps are not for everyone, but they are useful to most. They are much better at finding you a mate then your are in a personal setting. Not just a little better but several orders of magnitude better. I personally will never try the old way
